The paper proposes a new block for 3D Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) that improves their feature learning capabilities while reducing computational and memory requirements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses the proposed block to achieve state-of-the-art results on 3D datasets, indicating that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
